          <h2 id="automated-codes">Setting Up Automated Guest Codes</h2>
          <p>The real power of a smart lock for Airbnb hosting isn't the hardware. It's the automation layer that sits on top. When your lock integrates with property management software, the workflow looks like this:</p>

          <ol>
            <li><strong>Booking confirmed:</strong> Your PMS receives the reservation from Airbnb, VRBO, or direct booking.</li>
            <li><strong>Code generated automatically:</strong> The software creates a unique PIN code tied to the guest's check-in and checkout times.</li>
            <li><strong>Guest receives instructions:</strong> An automated message is sent to the guest with their unique code and check-in instructions, typically 24-48 hours before arrival.</li>
            <li><strong>Code activates at check-in time:</strong> The lock only accepts the guest's code starting at the scheduled check-in hour.</li>
            <li><strong>Code expires at checkout:</strong> Automatically deactivated at the checkout time. No manual intervention required.</li>
            <li><strong>Access log updated:</strong> Every use of the code is recorded for review if needed.</li>
          </ol>

          <p>This entire workflow runs without you touching anything. A guest books your property at 2 a.m., and by morning they have their unique code waiting in their inbox, set to expire the moment they check out. No phone calls, no key handoffs, no wondering whether the previous guest's code still works.</p>

