              <h4>Emergency Lockbox</h4>
              <p>Mount a heavy-duty combination lockbox in a discreet but accessible location near the property. Store a physical key inside. Share the lockbox code only with guests after confirming they have exhausted other options. Change the code periodically.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
              <h4>Property Manager Access</h4>
              <p>Your property manager should always have a spare physical key for the property. In a lockout scenario, Nurture's team can coordinate emergency access within the hour for managed properties, ensuring guests are never left stranded.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
              <h4>Guest Instructions</h4>
              <p>Include clear troubleshooting steps in your check-in message: what to do if the PIN doesn't work, who to call, and where the backup access is. Guests who know what to do are far less likely to leave a negative review over a minor access hiccup.</p>
            </div>
