          <h3>Security Best Practices</h3>
          <p>Smart locks are significantly more secure than traditional keys or lockboxes when used correctly. These practices ensure you get the full security benefit:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Never reuse codes:</strong> Every booking gets a fresh, unique code. Even if the same guest books again, generate a new code for the new stay.</li>
            <li><strong>Set codes to activate at check-in time:</strong> A code that works starting 3 p.m. on check-in day cannot be used by the previous guest to access the property at 1 p.m. to retrieve a forgotten item without your knowledge.</li>
            <li><strong>Review the audit trail after each stay:</strong> A quick check of the access log confirms the code was only used during the booking window. Any anomalies are visible immediately.</li>
            <li><strong>Enable low-battery notifications:</strong> Set alerts at 25% and 10% so you always have advance warning before a battery failure.</li>
            <li><strong>Update firmware regularly:</strong> Smart lock manufacturers release security patches. Enable automatic firmware updates or check manually every few months.</li>
          </ul>

